%TAG !u! tag:unity3d.com,2011:
--- !u!114 &11400000
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 70ee8ab7554a13a4d9d7566ffc03ae8b, type: 3}
  m_Name: '#1 Bestseller'
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::FlightPaper.ProjectSorrow.Encounters.EncounterScriptableObject
  id: 11
  title: '#1 Bestseller'
  description: 'Your peers are discussing their thoughts on a popular new bestseller.


    Everyone
    is singing its praises. After going around and giving their thoughts, the group
    turns to you for yours.


    You haven''t read the novel because you''ve never
    cared for the author''s previous works, but you do want to be a part of the discussion.'
  options:
  - title: Lie and say you liked it
    description: Become <color=#A1740E>Popular</color> <color=#828282>(x3)</color>
      and <color=red>Anxious</color> <color=#828282>(x3)</color>
    requirement: test
    conclusion: 'You just repeat some of the points other people made without getting
      too specific.


      Everyone one else nods in agreement. Luckily, the group''s
      focus doesn''t stay on you for long as someone in the group can''t contain
      their excitement and begins going on about their own thoughts on the book.'
    isHidden: 0
    item: {fileID: 0}
    consumable: {fileID: 0}
    tag: Popular
  - title: Lie and say you didn't care for it
    description: Become <color=purple>Stubborn</color> <color=#828282> (x4)</color>,
      <color=red>-3</color> reputation
    requirement: 
    conclusion: 'Thinking back to what you hated about the author''s previous books,
      you begin complaining about the prose.


      Seeing the group''s frustrations
      encourages to be even more of a contrarian. You talk about how the writing
      is derivative and hack. The more people push back, the more you double down.


      The
      author gets too much credit in your mind, and it''s your job to let people
      know.'
    isHidden: 0
    item: {fileID: 0}
    consumable: {fileID: 0}
    tag: Stubborn
  - title: Admit you haven't read it
    description: Become Serious <color=#828282>(x2)</color>, <color=red>-1</color>
      confidence
    requirement: 
    conclusion: 'Not wanting to lie, you fess up to having not read the book. You
      admit that everyone makes the book sound interesting, but you also didn''t
      care for the author''s last book.


      The group quickly moves on to discussion
      their favorite aspects of the book. You feel left out of the conversation,
      so you end up leaving shortly thereafter.'
    isHidden: 0
    item: {fileID: 0}
    consumable: {fileID: 0}
    tag: Serious
  minRound: 1
